    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-12-03T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-12-03T08:00:00-05:00" n="185"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.00 Revolutions/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-03T07:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 3, 1931—7 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>97. Revolution broke out last night and controls the city completely which
                    history shows probably means final success. President is bringing troops from
                    Santa Tecla.<note n="1" xml:id="d185fn1">For correction of this statement, see
                        par. 2 of despatch No. 26, December 15, from the Minister in El Salvador,
                            <ref target="#pg_197">p. 197</ref>.</note> I am trying to minimize
                    bloodshed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
